# dpkg/apt - Packages to install via apt-get for ALL LoxBerry/Debian versions.
#
# LoxBerry runs "apt-get install -y <package>" for each non-empty, non-comment
# line in this file during plugin installation. One package name per line.
# Use exact package names as you would pass them to apt-get.
#
# Selection logic (only ONE apt file is used per installation):
#   1. dpkg/apt<DEBIAN_VERSION>  e.g. apt12 (Bookworm), apt13 (Trixie)  <- preferred
#   2. dpkg/apt<LB_MAJOR>        e.g. apt3, apt2  (obsolete, do not use for new plugins)
#   3. dpkg/apt                  this file, used as fallback if no version-specific file exists
#
# For architecture-specific .deb packages (not from the repository), place them
# in subdirectories named after the CPU architecture:
#   dpkg/armv6l/   Raspberry Pi 1, Zero (32-bit ARMv6)
#   dpkg/armv7l/   Raspberry Pi 2 Rev.1 (32-bit ARMv7)
#   dpkg/aarch64/  Raspberry Pi 2-4, Zero 2 (64-bit ARM)
#   dpkg/x86_64/   x86 64-bit (VirtualBox VM etc.)
#   dpkg/riscv64/  RISC-V 64-bit
#
# Only list packages not already installed by default on LoxBerry.
# Unnecessary installations slow down plugin setup for all users.
#
# Examples:
# libwww-perl
# python3-requests
# jq
